Proxmox Debian VE:
  - SSL for hypervisor web server
  - Fail2Ban listening on hypvisor webserver interface
  - NO openssh-server / vsftp installed (DISABLES sftp, ftp, ssh, services!)
  - UFW:
      - ufw allow from localnetwork/24
      - ufw default deny incoming
      - ufw default allow outgoing
      - deny port 20-22 (?)
  - Multi-factor Authentication via OTP (?)
      
UBUNTU 16 VM:
 SSH
 - NON-standard port
 - SSH Keys
 - Disable password authentication, keys only
 - Disable root login (openssh default)
 FTP
  - Disable entirely via uninstalling vsftp, use sftp via openssh-server
 SFTP
 - NON-standard port
 - Disable root login
 FIREWALL
  - sudo ufw default deny incoming
  - sudo ufw default allow outgoing
  - ufw allow from localnetwork/24 [to any port <>]
  - ufw allow <port>
FAIL2BAN
  - On SSH / FTP interface
Multi-Factor Authentication via libpam-google-authenticator

